cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.DB, cs.CY

This paper is primarily focused on the detection of financial crimes using machine learning and graph learning approaches. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a methodology for sharing information across institutions, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The use of a federated graph learning platform also suggests that it could belong to cs.DB (Databases) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
